The paper proposes distributed algorithms for two well-established problems that operate efficiently under extremely harsh conditions. These problems are related to network and graph theory, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NE), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Game Theory (cs.GT). Given that the paper deals with distributed algorithms for network and graph problems, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates.
